							Naive Bayes:

Naive Bayes is a supervised classification algorithm based on Bayes' Theorem. It predicts the probability of a data point belonging to a class by assuming that the input features are independent. The four main types are Gaussian Naive Bayes (continuous data), Multinomial Naive Bayes (count data), Bernoulli Naive Bayes (binary data), and Complement Naive Bayes (imbalanced datasets). Due to its simplicity, speed, and effectiveness, Naive Bayes is widely used in spam filtering, sentiment analysis, document classification, and medical diagnosis.

